author: GREG MATTURA
title: H.S. girls volleyball: Lakeland looks semi-tough - Girls Volleyball
text:
Keeping the ball in play has kept Lakeland well above .500 and still alive in the Passaic County girls volleyball tournament.
The Lancers make their first appearance in the Passaic tournament semifinals since 2010 when they host favored Clifton at 5 p.m., Wednesday. Seeded third, Lakeland (11-5) has earned the chance to face perennial contender and No. 2 Clifton (16-5) because its hitters have shown greater accuracy this season.
"Even though we may not be hitting the ball as hard, we’re keeping the ball in play more," said Lancers coach Jim Phillips.
In the 6:30 p.m. semifinal Wednesday at Lakeland, top-seeded Wayne Valley (14-4) faces No. 5 DePaul (5-6). The semifinal survivors advance to the final, 5 p.m. Saturday at Clifton. 
Phillips, a Lakeland alum, said hitting errors "plagued us" in previous seasons, but "with another year of experience, they’re hitting the ball better and they’re approaching the ball better."
Senior Morgan Burke and junior Michelle Froehlich have made significant improvement. Senior Emma Spero continues to be consistent, and junior Kaeli Ryan has stepped it up.
Lakeland and Clifton have not faced each this season in a best-of-three match. They both competed at the Clifton Invitational and Passaic Invitational, with the Mustangs advancing further both times.
Traditionally, Lakeland and Clifton have taken turns hosting the semifinals and finals, and Wednesday marks the first time this group of Lancers changes from spectators to players.
"It’s very raucous and loud even when we’re not in it," Phillips said of his gym in Wanaque, "so I hope we can get a lot of support and make it even more raucous and loud and crazy."
QUICK HITS: Coach Caryn Schanstine, in her 13th season at Northern Highlands, earned her 200th victory with a 25-11, 25-9 win over Hackensack a week ago. … Rutherford senior M Jessica Rogers became the first in program history to surpass 1,000 kills during a 25-17, 25-9 win a week ago over Hawthorne, while sophomore S Anna DeCesare has 333 assists this season entering Monday’s action. … Senior H Jenna Berry led Fair Lawn to a 4-0 week, featuring an upset over Wayne Valley, and totaled 36 kills, 38 digs and 27 service points (including six aces). … Hawthorne senior L Barbara Colizza had a busy two games, collecting 38 digs in a three-set loss to Garfield and 18 in a Passaic quarterfinal loss to Clifton. … Saddle Brook senior H Caitlin Ryan eclipsed 100 kills for the season during Wednesday’s 25-14, 25-10 win over Westwood. … Standings for the Big North and NJIC can be found on Varsity Aces’ Web page: northjersey.com/varsityaces.
STATE TOURNAMENT: Wednesday is the cutoff for the state tournament, and according to the NJSIAA, "All teams .500 or better and some teams below .500, according to power rating points … may be seeded."
